quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,72,"She said, “Alas for me!<sup>39</sup> How can I bear a child while I am an old woman, and this is my husband, an old man? This is a strange thing indeed!”","[39] An expression of astonishment and amazement."
  11,73,"They said, “Are you amazed at the decree of Allah? May Allah’s mercy and blessings be upon you, O people of the house<sup>40</sup>. He is Praiseworthy, All-Glorious.”","[40] i.e., Abraham’s (عليه السلام) household."
  11,74,"When the shock of fear left Abraham and the glad tidings [of Isaac’s birth] came to him, he started pleading with Us<sup>41</sup> concerning the people of Lot.","[41] i.e., with Our angels."
  11,75,"Abraham was indeed forbearing, tenderhearted<sup>42</sup>, and constantly returning in repentance.","[42] i.e., supplicating with humility out of fear of Allah."
  11,76,"[The angels said], “O Abraham, leave this<sup>43</sup>, for indeed the command of your Lord has already come to pass, and there will come upon them a punishment that cannot be averted.”","[43] Abraham was to intercede on their behalf."
  11,77,"When Our messengers<sup>44</sup> came to Lot, he was perturbed and felt troubled on their account<sup>45</sup>, and said, “This is a distressing day.”","[44] i.e., angels. [45] He feared for the safety and honor of his guests."
  11,78,"His people came rushing to him, and they were accustomed to committing evil deeds<sup>46</sup>. He said, “O my people, here are my daughters<sup>47</sup> [for marriage]; they are purer for you. So fear Allah and do not disgrace me concerning my guests. Is there not a right-minded man among you?”","[46] i.e., sodomy and homosexual rape of males.\n [47] Or the women of his community."
  11,79,"They said, “You already know that we have no need for your daughters, and you surely know what we want!”",""
  11,80,"He said, “Would that I had some strength [to stop you] or could rely on a mighty support!”",""
  11,81,"[The angels said], “O Lot, we are messengers of your Lord; they can never reach you. So set out with your family in the dark part of the night, and none of you should look back, except your wife; she will suffer the same fate as the others. Their appointed time is the morning; is not the morning near?”",""
